org.knime.core.node.port.inactive

Interface InactiveBranchConsumer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActiveBranchInverterNodeModel, BreakpointNodeModel, CaseEndNodeModel, EndcaseNodeModel, EndifNodeModel, GenericCatchNodeModel, GlobalTimerinfoNodeModel, TimerinfoNodeModel, VirtualSubNodeOutputNodeModel

    public interface InactiveBranchConsumer
    Marker interface implemented by nodes (NodeModel) that are able to consume inactive branches. The configure and execute methods of such implementations must accept classes of InactiveBranchPortObject and InactiveBranchPortObjectSpec (which kind of violates the assertions made by the method API).

    This interface is implemented by nodes such as the End IF and End Case node.

    Author:
    B. Wiswedel, University of Konstanz
